{
  "stem": "7414.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I played till-- at home for my own pleasure and for a time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And now I don't know if I would even remember [LAUGHS] after such a long time.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That is very important to describe the town because it has a historical significance afterwards and during-- you will hear afterwards, during the war.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Przemysl is situated in the south in the center between Lwow and Krakaow.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It is divided by a River San.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a very nice town, really nice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Whoever talks even know about Przemysl-- it is a little bit-- was a little bit like here, Sydney, on the hill because we were very close to Karpaty.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a very hilly country.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were divided nearly evenly between those three nationalities.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Like we were 20-- 20-odd thousand Polish people, 23,000 Jews, and 20-odd thousand Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They lived mostly on the edge of the town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the center was the old Jewish quarter.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And most of the Jews who were business people-- they had shops.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had [INAUDIBLE], and professions-- professions like lawyers and this.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were in the center of the town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mentioned that specially, that-- the River San because afterwards when the Russian and Stalin and Hitler divided Poland between themselves, San was the border.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On the left side, the Polish side, were Germans, and on our side, we belonged to-- we were under Stalin occupation.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So and the river, which divided us, was very easy to cross.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The bridge was still standing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Anyway, the tine-- town was quite peaceful for a long time, perhaps because it was such a balance between all those three nationalities.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
